wiki.content: Throughout “Man of the Year,“ Juice WRLD uses an upbeat, rock-influenced instrumental to vocalizes a track about his struggles with drugs and love. Despite his fame, he still can’t seem to find his happiness, and he touches on using his significant other’s strength to keep him together. He first previewed this track on July 5, 2019. The track resurfaced with leaks one day prior to Juice’s posthumous album Legends Never Die. On July 13, 2020, the track’s chorus and second verse were changed, being reverted to its original leaked version on streaming platforms after fans expressed dislike for the new version.
